                            U.S. BANKRUPTCY COURT

                        SOUTHERN DISTRICT OF INDIANA

                                   NOTICE

                 AMENDMENT TO STATEMENT OF FINANCIAL AFFAIRS

   The Statement of Financial Affairs (Official Bankruptcy Form 7) has
   been amended to provide additional information. Four new questions have
   been added to the form concerning:

     •
     community property owned by a debtor and the debtor's non-filing
     spouse or former spouse (question 16)

     • environmental information (question 17)

     • any consolidated tax group of a corporate debtor (question 24)

     • the debtor's contributions to any employee pension fund (question
     25)

   In addition, every corporate or partnership debtor and every individual
   or joint debtor who has been in business within six years before filing
   the petition must answer questions 19-25.

   The amended form is available from the Internet at:

     • www.uscourts.gov/bankform/

     • www.uscourts.gov, click on "For Public Review", scroll down and
     click on "Federal Rulemaking"' then click on "Official Bankruptcy
     Forms

   The amended form is EFFECTIVE NOW, but until the new form becomes
   widely available, bankruptcy case trustees and creditors who need the
   additional information required by the form must request the debtor to
   fumish it separately, either at the meeting of creditors or by other
   means.

   Dated: January 4, 2001

   JOHN A. ONEAL, CLERK

